<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-4274] MDCUnitOfWork behaviour incorrect with nested routes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-4274</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;MDCUnitOfWork.clear() removes any content set by MDCUnitOfWork from MDC.&lt;br/&gt;
If there are two separate exchange running at the same time in the same thread, as happens when a ProduceTemplate is used from Java, this is incorrect because the MDC of the parent is cleared after the child completes.&lt;br/&gt;
Conceptually the MDC should be a stack, but MDC only accepts strings so the simplest thing to do is for MDCUnitOfWork to replace the previous values in clear().&lt;/p&gt;</description>
